caption: Last week was the first time we went to this magnificent restaurant. But It is obviously not the last. We enjoyed the evening very much with the excellent service, with the excellent  meal and wine and with the comfortable pay. We will surely come back in a short time.
This place never disappoints. They have awesome dishes for reasonable rates, there are no long waits even when they are packed.

Poor management, cost cutting and cheap containers make their delivery inedible and literally a waste of money....gave them a chance with a hefty order of nearly $200 that they botched and refused to make right. Save your time and appetite for a restaurant that cares - Jai Dee isn't it. We literally had plastic in our food from the lids on their containers shattering and they gave us the runaround when we brought it to their attention. Shameful behavior and unsanitary.
I would give it another chance if I'm in the area,  but won't order those chicken wings again. People who like their wings must also order wings from Domino's Pizza.

Jaidee always amazes me with delicious plates. From the eggplant basil to their various curries and noodle dishes, their food is exceptional every time. All of their proteins are terrific, especially their seitan and chicken. Undoubtedly one of the most consistent restaurants in Park Slope!
Really tasty, large portions, reasonably priced.
Excellent food every time!
Like the food. Portions a bit small but tasty! And they do it proper Thai spicy if you ask
Food was super tasty! Keep in mind that if you order curry and want rice, it will add $2 or 2.50 to the price.
One of my main spots to eat. good location, well organised, and good customer service. I recommend this place!
Great khao soi and green curry!
I recomend this place to eat .
Outstanding experience!
Friendly staff and great food - and very reasonably priced!!
Good taste and friendly staffs

Jai Dee was a surprise. all around good neighborhood Thai restaurant. nothing will blow you away but everything we had was good. I was impressed by the healthy serving vegetables that accompanied each dish
Liked it.   New owners.   Still a good place to enjoy a meal

Cozy Thai place with very tasty dishes. The appetizers,  chicken satay, spring rolls, dumplings,  are  very good and the entrees are  delicious. They need extra set of hands, the waiter had too much on his plate.
The worst Thai food ever and I tried many around the world, in Thailand and NYC! Avoid!
This place was hands down one of the worst places that I ever ate Thai Food. Horrible flavors. Terribly cooked vegetables. Even the wine was bad. I do not understand these positive reviews.
A nice afternoon with some great thai :)
Red Curry with shrimp was amazing. The Thai noodle soup was nice and light with a savory clear broth, bok choy and rice noodles. Everything was delicious, my new favorite Thai spot!
Very cozy,delishious food ,friendly staf,soft jazz music..... Clean bathroom.... Food was made on order ,so it was hot and fresh, Let me talk about dessert, litttt.... Absolutely 5 stars.....

(Translated by Google) [ENG] The food tastes very good and the price is very comfortable compared to the restaurants in the area. The attention was excellent.  (Original) [ESP] La comida tiene muy buen sabor y el precio es muy cómodo comparado a los restaurantes de la zona.  La atención fue excelente.
Great little restaurant. Friendly, accommodating staff and good vegetarian options, if that's your thing.
The customer service is always swift, lovely vibes, very welcoming staff. Will visit again when I am in the area.

A lovely surprise! We came about 1.5 hours before closing on a weekday and were the only ones. It's a great place for a quick, casual, and romantic date. Had the bacon pad thai (how can you not try that!) and drunken noodle with crab. Also tom kha soup and a salad. Everything was very yummy, service was great, and it's totally reasonably priced. Plus the music is pleasant and not too loud or distracting. And their tables seem spaced well apart, for when it's more crowded.
A tiny, casual restaurant with attentive service, very good food carefully presented.
We loved everything we ordered! Especially try the red curry! What a 7th Avenue gem.
Food excellent and cheerful, quantity small

No one beats Jai Dee's pad see u delicious everytime. And I love the vegetable dumpling steamed and fried!! Thanks jai dee for being consistent. Their delivery guy is awesome too hes always polite, cheerful, and he bring the food all the way to my desk  great experience overall

We stopped by randomly during a local contest as we love Thai food and everyone in our group enjoyed their meals. We ordered different items from the lunch special and it was the perfect serving. The spices were delicious and authentic. 😋 Yum! Definitely a gem in Park Slope.

Had a great salmon in Panang curry special, food was very good and well priced.  I wish certain items like what I ordered would include rice, but maybe that is typical for the area.  Friendly staff too!
Very enjoyable. Service was print, and pleasant and food was excellent.
Definitely my favorite Thai food in Brooklyn and a great price point for the neighborhood.  Food is fresh and not too heavy.  I def recommend checking out before a movie.

Wow. I dont understand how good this place is. Truly an exceptional experience. Exceptionally amazing service from the first second we walked in till we walked out. Intuitive wait staff. Very hard working. And the food, wow. Wow We will b back many more times to explore the menu

Taste was good. Space was definitely low-key. But portions were small, rice was extra, and there was a minimum for using card of $20. I got the Green Curry with a Thai Iced Coffee. All under $20, but if I didn't have cash I would have had to get something else or get hit with an ATM fee (didn't see an ATM in the restaurant btw). All those factors lead me to not go back. Overall, skip it or just order delivery.
Tasty food with good service.
Nice staff. Quiet restaurant where you can hear your dinner company talk! Decent green curry.
First Thai restaurant my significant other and I tried in Brooklyn. Very authentic vibe. The food was very good and fairly priced!
great food, look forward to my next visit!
Delicious eggplant shrimp dish and pad thai!

REALLY good glass noodles and pad Thai, yummy coconut juice and coconut sticky rice, friendly service, decent prices. Only problem was that  the mango that came with the coconut sticky rice was totally unripe :-(   I'll probably come again when I'm in the area, and just skip dessert.
Went there for my birthday with my husband. Great food. Oh how I missed thai ice tea and green tea ice cream. So glad they have them both.

Good Thai food that's served in a quaint space. I went for a family dinner and the staff was very friendly, even when we ordered way too much food for three people. :)  The entrance is accessible though a bit weird to navigate, as is seating. I did not use the restroom so I can't comment on it.

The nastiest thai food I've ever tasted. I ordered a beef dish and it taste like fish. I ordered orange chicken and received a piece of fried chicken breast, one piece of broccoli, two carrots, and iceberg lettuce w/ sauce that is so sweet I think it would do better as a dessert sauce. Please do not let the ratings this restaurant has sway you to buy food from here. I tried to eat thiz food when I was very hungry and still could not bring myself to eat It. It is absolutely disgusting. I am sorry to even have to write this about someone's business but I feel it is my duty to save people from wasting their money like I did.
I ordered from this place it cost me to much money and get little food   mad as hell
Decent thai place; tasteful decor and friendly staff. The green curry was very good.
Good thai spot
Amazing Thai food - ordering for pickup is quick, food is always fresh and lots of variety!
FLAVORS WERE ON POINT!,AND PRICES ARE REASONABLE..
Excellent
Great food great value, nice service and clean dining room.

Here we go again... I went to this restaurant probably 6/7 times and will go again soon whenever I crave some authentic Thai food. If you have ever been to Thailand and loved Thai fried fish then try this little restaurant in Brooklyn who can take you back to Thailand with their special fried fishes. Owner was extremely friendly and understood what I was actually looking for. Definitely going to this place many more times.
I love this place. My family and I have been coming here for over ten years. It use to go by the name Watana. Thankfully, same great food, ambiance and excellent service. BEST TAI in Brooklyn!

For the price the service is great the interior is good and the food quality is very good! I like being cozy, replaced and comfortable. I liked the way they present plates. Clean and neat! The taste is great for Thai good!
Great food. Shame it doesn’t get busier in the restaurant as the food is delicious and service lovely. Also can BYOB for $9 corkage. We were happy.

This place is ok for take out, but really good for eat in. Really great Tom Yum soup and curry. They also have good lunch specials, and some amazing drink specials. I think a lot of people order out from here, because the restaurant itself is generally empty.
Great food and service.
Simply delicious! The duck is fantastic.
Good and friendly
Wonderful service, can't think of a single issue. Definitely coming back
Affordable, friendly and great Thai. Super cute inside decorations too.
Great neighborhood gem!
Consistently good! Use Jai Dee for takeout and eat in, great every time. By far the best Thai in Park Slope.
My go-to place for the best Thai food in Park Slope. Good vegan options—request no eggs when ordering the Pad Thai. Excellent steamed veggie dumplings. Nice atmosphere! Very quick delivery.
Good food. Amazing prices. Not the biggest fan of Thai food, but this place makes it yummy!
Great price. Great Food. 100% Recommended.

Came here  and i got to say the food better. I tried the pad Thai noodles and also the coconut soup also tried the drunken noodle.  The chefs add extra flavoring and the pad Thai noodles was cooked very well. Very chewy and tender . Also they added a good amount of noodles. The drunken noodles was also Divine and had a great amount of heat. Lots of green peppers , onions  and lots of spice. Which is a plus.  The only complaint was the thai ice tea.  It was a bunch of ice and i asked them for less ice. But they was soo gracious to not include the thai ice tea in the bill and gave me a another one with little ice. That great customer service. Also the coconut soup had that coconut taste i been longing for. My taste buds was extremely satisfied with the fresh taste.  And the people working there including the owner was very nice, caring and attentive. I will continue doing business in this establishment

Just ordered drunken noodle, pad thai with beef, mango salad and spring rolls. Ordered through the restaurant. Great customer service and fast delivery. The food is delicious, definitely worth it. Recommended!
Tasty, Delicious, and great services! Love it here!
We usually go here for lunch. The food is OK although the selection is not very good. Prices are fair, service is OK.
Good food with thoughtful selection
Love the pad Thai. Great people. Calm ambiance.  Excellent food for the price.
Great food!  Great staff!  I will be back!
The seitan here is pretty good
Always good food
One of the best Thai places in the neighborhood.
Delicious and authentic Thai food in a nice inviting restaurant. You Definitely get your money's worth. I'll be back again!!
Very good Thai dishes with affordable price. Make sure you also have the Thai beer they serve there.
Excellent food and service. The family owners were nice and kind to everyone. I'm very satisfied with everything they provide. No wonder why people call them Jai Dee. Will come back again for sure.

Great first time experience. The cuisine was delicious. I had spicy rice noodles with chicken; I would recommend this dish. I enjoyed my entire experience from the design of the restaurant to it's food. This establishment provided me with excellent Thai cuisine and a nice area for events holding up to 60 people. With an A health grade and good food they are bound to be successful.
awesome place... the food was great
